manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Question & Answer Is this a mechanical keyboard? It’s a membrane keyboard. There is no loud "clicking" sound when typing. How loud is this keyboard? What type of noise do these make? Our gaming keyboard is not mechanical. So it's not very loud when you typing. Can I turn off the light on this keyboard? Press the FN+Application key （check the user manual）to turn on/ turn off the backlight. Can I customize RGB? This gaming keyboard is not RGB. But you can adjust the brightness and breathing speed of the backlit according to your preference. Can I switch out the keycaps and buy different keycaps if I'd like? Detachable, but there is no universal keycap version available on the market. How long is the cord? The cord is 1.8m（23.62inch）.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I appreciate that the silent keyboard is compact and lightweight
reviews.reviewText: The silent keyboard has been a game-changer for me in terms of productivity and comfort. This keyboard is designed to be quieter than traditional keyboards, making it an excellent option for people who work in shared spaces or who prefer a quieter typing experience.The keys are responsive and comfortable to type on, with a satisfying tactile feedback that helps me to type accurately and quickly. The keyboard is also designed to reduce the strain on my hands and wrists, which is important for anyone who spends a lot of time typing.I appreciate that the silent keyboard is compact and lightweight, making it easy to move around and take with me on the go. It's also easy to set up and use, with no complicated software or drivers required.The design of the silent keyboard is sleek and modern, with a slim profile that looks great on my desk. It's available in a variety of colors, so I was able to choose one that fits my style and personality.Overall, I highly recommend the silent keyboard to anyone who wants a quieter, more comfortable typing experience. It's a high-quality product that has improved my productivity and reduced my typing-related discomfort.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of, if not the best cheap gaming keyboard! 5/5!
reviews.reviewText: Have owned this keyboard for a few months now and I must say its superior to many other keyboards I have had in the past. The RGB light still is functioning, the clicks are quiet enough that I don't hear them and none of the keys have worn out. Partially it could be in such good shape as I clean it often and is good maintenance for any keyboard.The only con is some of the lettering does get scratched pretty easily but I believe that more user error than defect or faulty issue. Definitely recommend this keyboard for gaming as well as office work. Love the backlights as I can switch them off but I rarely do. Will update if anything changes. 5/5!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great feel and function
reviews.reviewText: It is the perfect replacement. The keys work very well and have a very positive feel, almost a mechanical feel without the "pop". This feature allows a great typing experience that will most likely lessen typing errors or accidental key strokes. Lighting is very nice and complete.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a keyboard that looked cool, was comfortable, and had the separate numeric keypad. This one checks all those boxes. My laptop keyboard is very clumsy for my fingers and I often have trouble typing. I thought this keyboard could improve that, and it does. The keys are easy to find and press and the response is great. One thing I notice is that the color scheme seems to continually reset to standard on rather than the strobe setting I like. Not sure if that is from me hitting the programming key or if there is a timeout on the strobe setting. I have nothing bad to say about the keyboard; it just didn't blow me away as much as I thought it would. I give it a B+.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and comfortable, but beware...
reviews.reviewText: Updated 10/4/2023 - I have had this keyboard all of 2 months and some of the paint on the keys has begun to wear off. Very similar to the other reviews. I still love the keyboard for the feel, sound and lights but very disappointed that this is happening, I will have to replace in less than a year. I give it another few months before the keys have nothing left on them. Down grading my review because of this.Original Review - I bought this to replace a mechanical keyboard. I thought I was going to like the mechanical clicking and I was wrong. It was just too loud for me. Now this keyboard is so much more quiet. I love the soft touch and click of the keys. I can also type faster on this than I could on the mechanical one. The keys are very responsive. I wish it had more color changing options like the mechanical one I had but it is still pretty to look at. I bought this for work and so far so good. I am very happy with the cost and the quality of this keyboard.
